<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Unfortuantely, I think that's basically how the spell is supposed to work. It's a pulse spell; every 6 seconds or so it pulses and "renews" the charm. You will know that it has done so because the charmed mob will have little music notes around him. You can (or at least i can) stop the charm by "casting" it again, target another mob, and send the charmed mob at your target within the approx. 6 second window you have after a pulse. After that the creature is no longer under your direct control; however, he will continue to attack the target. It's a pain in the ass and needs to be worked on no doubt. However, they really need to make it so that you are able to target other creatures without it attempting to charm them. Also, it is VERY sad how very few humanoid creatures are considered humanoid by the game. For example, lunatishees... they look like little people, right? They have a basic human structure, right? They are humanoids, right? Not according to DAoC. I can only hope that this spell does get worked on, it needs it.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
